                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On September 13, 1944, Hull sent to Roosevelt a memorandum on shipment of arms to
                    Ethiopia so that the President would be prepared if Churchill raised the
                    question at the forthcoming Quebec Conference. For the text of Hull’s
                    memorandum, see <ref target="frus1944v05#pg_73">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1944, vol. V, pp. 73</ref>–<ref
                        target="frus1944v05#pg_74">74</ref>. No indication has been found that the
                    subject of the memorandum was actually discussed by Roosevelt and Churchill at
                    Quebec.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
